    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--vertical-rule opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        “Everyone Will Die in Prison”: How Louisiana’s Plan to Lock People Up Longer Imperils Its Sickest Inmates
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1  article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <span class="name">Richard A. Webster</span>, <a href="https://veritenews.org/">Verite News</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-03-28EDT05:00">March 28, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

        <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
        <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" >            Janice Parker has witnessed the failing medical care at Angola, the state’s largest prison, on her frequent visits to see her paralyzed son. Laws passed at the behest of Gov. Jeff Landry threaten to further strain that system.
        </h2>
    </div>
    
</div>
        
